Vergil — kill criterion test set (tests/kill_criterion_month2/)
===============================================================

The Solidity contracts under `project/src/` are Vergil-original
reference implementations of the ERC-20, ERC-721, and ERC-4626 token
standards. They follow the same on-chain semantics as the OpenZeppelin
contracts of the same name (most recently
https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts v5.x, MIT
licensed) for the properties the Phase 2 kill criterion verifies, but
they are not literal copies of upstream OZ source. We chose this
single-file approach so Halmos can compile each target without a deep
import graph, and so the contracts ship under the project's Apache-2.0
license without dual-licensing concerns.

Behavioural notes:
  * ERC4626.sol inlines the underlying asset accounting as a uint256
    mapping rather than wrapping an external ERC-20 — this isolates the
    monotonicity / round-trip properties from any reentrancy concerns
    on an untrusted asset contract.
  * ERC721.sol does not implement IERC165 or `safeTransferFrom`'s
    IERC721Receiver callback — neither is part of the Phase 2 property
    set.
  * ERC20Pausable.sol's pauser is a single address set at deploy time;
    OZ's AccessControl + roles is out of scope for the Vergil kill
    criterion.
